  "prompt": "How do I stop thinking about dying?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful strategies to manage thoughts about death:\n\n1. Seek professional help\n- Talk to a therapist or counselor\n- Consider cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT)\n- Discuss anxiety or depression if present\n\n2. Practice mindfulness and relaxation techniques\n- Meditation\n- Deep breathing exercises\n- Yoga\n- Grounding techniques\n\n3. Challenge negative thoughts\n- Recognize when death-related thoughts are irrational\n- Reframe thoughts positively\n- Focus on living in the present moment\n\n4. Maintain a healthy lifestyle\n- Regular exercise\n- Balanced diet\n- Adequate sleep\n- Limit caffeine and alcohol\n\n5. Build meaningful connections\n- Spend time with loved ones\n- Cultivate supportive relationships\n- Join support groups\n\n6. Find purpose and meaning\n- Set personal goals\n- Engage in fulfilling activities\n- Practice gratitude\n- Explore spiritual or philosophical perspectives\n\n7. Reduce external triggers\n- Limit exposure to news and media that might provoke anxiety\n- Create a supportive environment\n\n8. Consider medication\n- Consult a psychiatrist about potential anti-anxiety medications\n\nIf thoughts about dying become overwhelming or persistent, professional help is recommended to address underlying issues.",
